### 1. One-Line Summary
Nittaku G-1 is a legendary, highly linear spin-offensive rubber with an exceptionally high throw arc, while Genextion is a modern, harder, power-oriented rubber designed to maximize top-end speed and heavy spin for the plastic ball era.

### 2. Head-to-Head Breakdown

* **Speed & Gears:**
    * **Low Impact:** Nittaku G-1 is manageable and strictly linear. Genextion feels a bit dead and requires active engagement to produce speed.
    * **Top End:** Genextion has a significantly higher maximum speed and power ceiling compared to Nittaku G-1.
    * **Linearity:** Nittaku G-1 is extremely linear (what you put in is what you get). Genextion exhibits a slight catapult effect only when hitting through its dense sponge at high impacts.

* **Spin Mechanics:**
    * **Opening Loop:** Nittaku G-1 is incredibly easy for lifting heavy backspin due to its high throw. Genextion requires more precise technique and deeper sponge engagement.
    * **Max Spin:** Both are excellent, but Genextion generates slightly heavier, more penetrating spin on full-power shots.
    * **Topsheet Grip:** Nittaku G-1 has legendary mechanical grip that bites the ball. Genextion features a highly advanced topsheet optimized specifically for the ABS ball, resisting slippage perfectly.

* **Flight Path (Throw Angle):**
    * **Arc Height:** Nittaku G-1 has a very high, pronounced, and looping arc. Genextion has a medium-high, much more forward-driving trajectory.
    * **Safety:** Nittaku G-1 provides a massive safety margin over the net. Genextion's lower trajectory can be riskier to play but is much harder for opponents to track and block.

* **Feel & Feedback:**
    * **Sensation:** Nittaku G-1 feels firm and direct. Genextion feels harder due to its denser sponge and offers a very solid, heavy sensation on big impacts.
    * **Dwell:** Nittaku G-1 offers excellent perceived dwell time. Genextion holds the ball well but releases it much faster upon full compression of the hard sponge.

* **Control & Short Game:**
    * **Sensitivity:** Nittaku G-1 is quite sensitive to incoming spin due to its grippy topsheet. Genextion is slightly less reactive on passive touches.
    * **Touch Play:** Both perform well, but Nittaku G-1's linearity makes dropshots and short pushes highly predictable and easy to execute.

* **Blocking & Countering:**
    * **Passive Block:** Genextion absorbs heavy topspin slightly better due to its harder sponge, whereas Nittaku G-1 can sometimes pop the ball up if the bat angle is off.
    * **Active Counter:** Genextion excels at aggressive counter-looping close to the table. Nittaku G-1 is very consistent but requires an active stroke to keep the counter-attack deep and threatening.

### 3. The Recommendation

* **Choose Genextion if:** You have high racket speed, prefer a harder sponge with a forward-driving trajectory, and want maximum power and heavy spin in counter-looping rallies.
* **Choose Nittaku G-1 if:** You rely on consistent heavy spin, prefer high safety margins over the net for opening loops, and value extreme linearity and precise control.